<span id="freeTextContainer3465567450546282280">I quite enjoyed the mellow yet vivid scope of the plot. For a novel where not a whole lot happens, I couldn&apos;t put the book down whenever I picked it up. The world feels lived in, and the characters were relatably flawed, despite the massively different alternate history/geopolitical makeup of the world. It did feel like it ended rather abruptly,but for the life of me, I cannot imagine a better ending.</span>
  <span id="freeText3465567450546282280" style="display:none">I quite enjoyed the mellow yet vivid scope of the plot. For a novel where not a whole lot happens, I couldn't put the book down whenever I picked it up. The world feels lived in, and the characters were relatably flawed, despite the massively different alternate history/geopolitical makeup of the world. It did feel like it ended rather abruptly,but for the life of me, I cannot imagine a better ending.</span>
